snippet.textDisplay:
From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
Chöying Drolma आनी छोइङ डोल्मा
Ani Chöying Drölma 2011.jpg
Chöying Drölma
Ani Choying Dolma (Nepali: आनी छोइङ डोल्मा) (born June 4, 1971, in Kathmandu, Nepal), also known as Choying Dolma and Ani Choying (Ani, "nun", is an honorific), is a Buddhist nun and musician from the Nagi Gompa nunnery in Nepal. She is known in Nepal and throughout the world for bringing many Tibetan Buddhist chants and feast songs to mainstream audiences.
